2.0 MVDV: Multi-Vector Data Validation
This section defines the heuristics used to calculate the Integrity Score (0.0 to 1.0) to identify Ghost Jobs.
A. Age Vector (V_age)
Logic: Proximity of "Date Posted" to current system time.
Formula:
If Age is less than or equal to 7 days: V_age = 1.0.
If Age is greater than 7 and less than or equal to 30 days: V_age = 1.0 - ((Age - 7) / 23).
If Age is greater than 30 days: V_age = 0.0 (Triggers baseline 40% Ghost Probability).
B. Frequency Vector (V_freq)
Logic: Triggers a flag if the same vanguard_id appears in consecutive scrape cycles.
Penalty: If hit_count is greater than 3 within 3 consecutive 30-day cycles, apply a 0.5x multiplier to the total Integrity Score.
C. Metadata Vector (V_meta)
Logic: Verifies employer domains and structural integrity.
Red Flag Penalties:
Domain Mismatch: -0.3 penalty if the listing does not exist on the hiring company's official Careers page.
Templated Content: -0.2 penalty for generic descriptions lacking specific team identifiers or project details.
D. Composite Integrity Score
Calculation: (V_age * 0.3) + (V_freq * 0.5) + (V_meta * 0.2).
Threshold: If Total Score is less than 0.4, set is_ghost_job to TRUE and set Disposition to "Expired".

3.0 Semantic Alignment Logic
This section defines the methodology for high-fidelity gap analysis between user profiles and leads.
A. Core Requirement Extraction
Process: Identify "Hard Skills" (Languages, Frameworks) and "Domain Expertise" required by the lead.
B. Experience Delta
Calculation: Experience_Delta = (Candidate_Years_Experience / Lead_Required_Years).
Constraint: Score caps at 1.0; values below 0.7 trigger a "Seniority Gap" flag.
C. Alignment Score
Calculation: Average of (Skill_Match_Rate + Experience_Delta + Seniority_Match).

4.0 System Thresholds and Automation Triggers
Ghost Job Probability: Any lead with an integrity_score below 0.4 is categorized as a "Ghost Job".
State Decay: Leads with a last_seen timestamp older than 30 days automatically transition to Expired.
Deduplication: SHA-256 hash of URL and Title must be verified against state.json before any logic execution.

